Nonstimulant Treatments
for ADHD
Jeffrey H. Newcorn, MDa,b,*, Beth Krone, PhDa, Ralf W. Dittmann, MSc, MD, PhDc
INTRODUCTION/HISTORY/DEFINITIONS/BACKGROUND
Overview, The use of nonstimulants in ADHD has a long history; the first publication of a
randomized, controlled clinical trial with imipramine was published almost 50 years
ago.1Since then, a variety of publications have attested to the utility of nonstimulants
in ADHD. Initially these medications were used “off-label” (ie, outside of FDA approval),
